        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 7:05PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 705 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Arley. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Arley, Helicon, Smith Lake, Bear Branch, Mill Branch, Panther Branch,
Wilson Bend, Hidden Cove Campground, and Cutoff Branch.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
